# ⚙️ SOP: Create & Run a systemd Service

## 1. Create service file

```bash
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/<service-name>.service
```

---

## 2. Add config

[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
WorkingDirectory=/home/mansi/Documents/Projects/Library-Management-System/Library-Management-System/backend

ExecStart=/root/.nvm/versions/node/v20.20.2/bin/npm run dev
Environment=PATH=/root/.nvm/versions/node/v20.20.2/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

Restart=always
Environment=NODE_ENV=development

 
[Service]
Type=simple
User=root
WorkingDirectory=/home/mansi/Documents/Projects/Library-Management-System/Library-Management-System/frontend

# Use NVM node + npm
ExecStart=/root/.nvm/versions/node/v20.20.2/bin/npm start

# Set PATH explicitly
Environment=PATH=/root/.nvm/versions/node/v20.20.2/bin:/usr/bin:/bin

Restart=always


---

## 3. Reload systemd

```bash
sudo systemctl daemon-reexec
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
```

---

## 4. Start service

```bash
sudo systemctl start <service-name>
```

---

## 5. Enable on boot (optional)

```bash
sudo systemctl enable <service-name>
```

---

## 6. Check status

```bash
systemctl status <service-name>
```

---

## 7. View logs

```bash
journalctl -u <service-name> -f
```

---

## 8. Restart / Stop

```bash
sudo systemctl restart <service-name>
sudo systemctl stop <service-name>

